g.name: Generation of the anchor cell: Two somatic gonadal cells are specified to become the anchor cell through an AC/UV decision.
Generation of VPCs: Six vulval precursor cells (VPCs) are specified among the 11 Pn.p cells.
Morphogenesis of the vulva: The seven types of vulval cells invaginate, and sequentially form seven distinct toroids, connects to the uterus, and everts as the hermaphrodite molts to adulthood.
